   \begin{center}
   \textbf{\Large{Ellipse, Natural Parametrization}}
   \end{center}
Equation:
\[
   \left(\frac{x}{a}\right)^2
   +
   \left(\frac{y}{b}\right)^2
   =1
\]
Parametrization:
\[
   \begin{pmatrix}
      x(t)\\y(t)
   \end{pmatrix}=
   a\begin{pmatrix}
      \cos{t}\\ \epsilon \sin{t}
   \end{pmatrix},
\]
$
\epsilon=\frac{b}{a}.
$
Take: $a=1.0$, $b=2.0$.
